==English==

===Etymology===
From the Latin ''dulce'' (sweet), ''See [[dulcimer]]''

===Adjective===
'''dulcet'''
# [[Sweet]], especially when describing voice or tones; [[melodious]]; [[harmonious]]
# Generally pleasing; [[soothing]]; [[agreeable]]
# Sweet to the taste (''archaic'')

